To get KaTeX to treat `$…$` as your inline‐math delimiters instead of (or in addition to) `\(...\)`, you basically need to change the parser’s default delimiter list. In your compiled bundle you should have (near the top of the parse code) something that looks roughly like:

```js
// somewhere in your lexer/parser setup
var defaultDelims = [
  { left: "\\(", right: "\\)", display: false },
  { left: "\\[", right: "\\]", display: true },
  /* maybe $$ / $$/ already */
];
```

What you want is to insert (or move) the `"$","$"` pair so that single‐dollars get recognized inline.  Find that `defaultDelims` (or similarly–named) array and modify it to:

```diff
 var defaultDelims = [
+  // first try double‐dollar (display)
+  { left: "$$", right: "$$", display: true },
+  // *then* single‐dollar (inline)
+  { left: "$",  right: "$",  display: false },
   // fall back to \( … \)
-  { left: "\\(", right: "\\)", display: false },
+  { left: "\\(", right: "\\)", display: false },
   // and finally \[ … \]
   { left: "\\[", right: "\\]", display: true }
 ];
```

If your compiled code doesn’t literally call it `defaultDelims`, look for the spot where it loops through `delims[i].left`/`right` trying to find a match, or where it builds an array of `{left: "...", right: "...", display: bool}`.

---

### A concrete diff example

Suppose in your compiled `parser.js` you see:

```js
var defaultDelims = [
    {left: "\\(", right: "\\)", display: false},
    {left: "\\[", right: "\\]", display: true},
    {left: "$$", right: "$$", display: true}
];
```

You would change it to:

```diff
 var defaultDelims = [
+    {left: "$$", right: "$$", display: true},
+    {left: "$",  right: "$",  display: false},
     {left: "\\(", right: "\\)", display: false},
     {left: "\\[", right: "\\]", display: true}
 ];
```

That way, when the lexer scans your input it will:

1. Match `$$…$$` first (display math),
2. Then match `$…$` (inline math),
3. Then fall back to `\(...\)` and `\[…\]` if no dollar delimiter was found.

---

### Alternative: configure via the public API

If you’re using the **auto-render** extension or the higher‐level `renderMathInElement`, you don’t have to touch the compiled core at all. Simply pass your own delimiter list:

```html
<script src="katex.min.js"></script>
<script src="auto-render.min.js"></script>
<script>
  renderMathInElement(document.body, {
    // override the defaults:
    delimiters: [
      {left: "$$", right: "$$", display: true},
      {left: "$",  right: "$",  display: false},
      {left: "\\(", right: "\\)", display: false},
      {left: "\\[", right: "\\]", display: true}
    ]
  });
</script>
```

That approach is safer (you’ll upgrade KaTeX without having to re-patch your bundle), but if you really need to mutate your compiled code directly, the `defaultDelims` diff above is all you need.
